        "questionText":  "What should not be done when deploying Cisco SD-Access in a brownfield environment?",
        "explanation":  "When deploying Cisco SD-Access in a brownfield environment, there will be live production traffic that you won\u0026rsquo;t want to interrupt or harm during the deployment of Cisco SD-Access. Because of this, Cisco Catalyst Center should not be leveraged to build out the underlay. In a greenfield situation with Cisco SD-Access, you can use Cisco Catalyst Center to automatically build out the underlay.\n\nWith a brownfield deployment of Cisco SD-Access, it is critical to make sure that all the devices, new and old, are listed on the Cisco SD-Access compatibility list. In addition, you must make sure your devices are running software levels that are also defined on the compatibility list. Failure to follow the compatibility list can result in future outages or uncertain behavior.",
        "difficulty":  "3",
        "comments":  "\u003cp\u003e12/29 - disregard Au query\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e4/3/24 Updated SDA to Cisco SD-Access and DNA Center to Cisco Catalyst Center -JG\u003c/p\u003e\n",
