        "explanation":  "Quality of Service (QoS) mechanisms manage network traffic to ensure critical applications receive priority. Common mechanisms include:\n\n- **Classification:** Identifying and categorizing traffic (e.g., by IP, protocol, application).\n- **Marking:** Setting a value in the packet header (e.g., DSCP) to indicate its QoS level, which is then used by other devices.\n- **Policing:** Enforcing a maximum traffic rate by dropping or remarking packets that exceed the configured rate.\n- **Shaping:** Smoothing out bursty traffic by delaying (buffering) excess packets to conform to a defined rate.\n\n- **Aggregation** is about combining multiple traffic flows, but it is not a direct QoS mechanism in the same sense as the others.",
