        "questionText":  "Comparing LLDP to LLDP-MED, which answers make a claim that applies to LLDP-MED but not LLDP? (Choose two answers.)",
        "explanation":  "The LLDP standard has used type-length-value (TLV) data structures since its original definition. For instance, the original LLDP standard defined TLVs that allow one device to inform a neighboring device about the first device\u0026rsquo;s name and port numbers used.\n\nUsing TLVs allows for easy future expansion of LLDP. LLDP Media Endpoint Discovery (LLDP-MED) refers to a set of endpoint-focused TLVs. LLDP-MED includes the TLVs that enable switches to inform an attached IP phone what voice VLAN ID to use on the link. As another example, LLDP TLVs support the IEEE Power over Ethernet (PoE) standards so that the powered device (PD) can use LLDP-MED to inform the attached switch of its power needs.",
