        "questionText":  "Assuming all default STP settings, which of SW3\u0026#39;s ports will become its root port, and what will its root cost be?",
        "explanation":  "Using the default port costs, a Gigabit Ethernet port will have a cost of 4 and a Fast Ethernet port will have a cost of 19. SW3 will have two interfaces that can be used to forward traffic to the root switch (SW4): through its Gi0/1 interface via SW1, which results in a total cost of 8, or via its Fa0/2 interface, which results in a total cost of 19. It will select the option with the lowest cost, so it will select its Gi0/1 interface as its root port with a cost of 8.\n\nSummarizing the competing potential root paths and their costs:\n\n\n\tSW3 G0/1 - SW1 G0/3\u0026nbsp; - 4 + 4 = 8\n\tSW3 G0/1 - SW1 G0/1\u0026nbsp;- SW2 G0/2\u0026nbsp; - 4 + 4 + 4 = 12\n\tSW3 F0/2\u0026nbsp; - 19",
        "difficulty":  "2",
        "comments":  "\u003cp\u003e10/13 - ok as-is \u0026quot;SW3\u0026rsquo;s root cost is the sum of the cost of the interfaces in the path from the switch to the root, in that case, SW3\u0026rsquo;s G0/1 (cost 4) plus SW1\u0026rsquo;s G0/3 (cost 4) for a total of 8.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI think you were picking the higher cost path from SW3 to SW1 to SW2 and then SW4, which would be cost 12, and therefore not the least cost path.\u0026quot;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e10/4, 9/28 - query to Au\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e5/31 - ok as-is \u0026quot;we agree that SW3\u0026rsquo;s RP is G0/1. It\u0026rsquo;s cost (default) is 4. Then, looking at SW1, also a non-root, it\u0026rsquo;s root port is SW1\u0026rsquo;s G0/3 port, which connects to the root switch, SW4. That adds 4 more. That gives the correct root cost of 8. I\u0026rsquo;m wondering if for some reason you believe SW1\u0026rsquo;s root port would be its G0/1 port? Or that SW2 would be root? Anyway, I believe the question is correct as is.\u0026quot;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e5/13, query to Au,\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e4/16 - ok as-is \u0026quot;All switches are configured with default STP settings, so SW4 becomes Root with the lowest value MAC address.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe link between SW3 and SW4 is a FastEthernet link, which has a default cost of 19. The links from SW3 up to SW1 and then down to SW4 are both GigabitEthernet which have a cost of 4 giving the total cost 8 for that path which is lower than 19 across the FastEthernet Link. SW3 will choose Gi0/1 as Root Port with a cost of 8. It is the sum of the cost of the interfaces in the path from the switch to the root, in that case, SW3\u0026rsquo;s G0/1 (cost 4) plus SW1\u0026rsquo;s G0/3 (cost 4) for a total of 8.\u0026quot;\u0026nbsp;\u0026nbsp;4/7, 6/28 - query to Au\u003c/p\u003e\n",
