        "questionText":  "DHCP Snooping has already been configured in the network shown in the figure, and you plan to add DAI configuration that relies on the DHCP Snooping Binding Table. Which answer shows the best configuration for switch SW2, specifically for VLAN 20?",
        "explanation":  "To properly enable DAI on switch 2 for VLAN 20, the following commands would need to be issued: The command ip arp inspection vlan 20 would be issued globally, which would also enable DAI on all ports assigned to VLAN 20, including trunk ports.\n\n\tThen, for ports connected to devices which do not lease an address with DHCP (servers, routers, switches, and so on), the configurartion should then trust the port so that DAI does not filter ARPs. To do so, the configuration adds the ip arp inspection trust command on switch SW2\u0026#39;s Gi0/12 port, which connects to the DHCP server, as well as Gi0/24, which connects to switch SW1. The correct answer does so by first using the interface range gi0/12,gi0/24 command to select both Gi0/12 and Gi0/24.",
        "difficulty":  "3",
        "comments":  "\u003cp\u003e10/13 - ok as-is, \u0026quot;SW1\u0026rsquo;s G0/2 port does not need to be included in the config that sets the ports to a DAI trusted state because the port needs to remain in the default of untrusted, as it is a port connected to an end-user device.\u0026quot;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e9/20 - query to Au\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e4/11 - Reader rescinds feedback, query to Au\u003c/p\u003e\n",
