        "explanation":  "Unless the configuration is saved to NVRAM, the switch will not use the updated configuration information, including the hostname, the next time it reboots. The show version shows a reboot, which could be due to loss of power and restoration of power, that occurred 1 day, 3 hours, and 24 minutes previous to when the user issued the show command, and that is when it reverted back to its original hostname.\n\nConfigurations may be saved to NVRAM, TFTP servers, and other destinations, but not to a configuration register. The exit command is not required to effect a change to a hostname, which happens automatically in RAM when Enter is pressed. Finally, there is no such thing as a permanent keyword on the hostname command.\u0026nbsp;",
